v0.2.19 fix auto-distance failures on Google Maps shares

Reported: sharing from Google Maps showed "Couldn't compute the distance" in the trip dialog.

Root causes:
1) maps.app.goo.gl short links don't contain an address — Nominatim can't geocode them.
2) Multi-line share text (Place / Street / City / URL) got joined with " . " by the mobile cleaner. The web geocoder treated this as a single noisy string and failed.
3) The dialog masked the real error with a generic message, making it hard to debug.

Fixes:
- web/src/app/api/distance/route.js:
  - Detect Google Maps URLs in the input; follow the redirect and extract coords from /@lat,lng or place name from /maps/place/... path.
  - Treat ". " and newlines as comma separators; strip http(s) URL fragments before geocoding.
  - Try the address-starting-with-a-number line first, then full string, then city+state.
- mobile/lib/services/location_distance_service.dart: estimate() now returns TripEstimateResult (estimate OR human-readable error) instead of nullable estimate.
- mobile/lib/screens/car_miles/car_miles_screen.dart: send the RAW shared text (not the cleaned bullet-joined version) to /api/distance so the server can resolve URLs and parse the address line. Surface the API error in the dialog helperText.
- mobile/pubspec.yaml: 0.2.18+28 -> 0.2.19+29
- web/src/app/download/page.jsx: bump to v0.2.19
